title: Republican hard-liners circumvent GOP leadership on Ex-Im bank
text: Many of the same centrist Republicans who complained about conservatives stabbing the GOP in the back on congressional procedures are behind the effort to circumvent their own leaders and force a vote on the divisive Export-Import Bank. Forty-two Republicans — less than a fifth of the House GOP conference — ... ...
